<lb n="1"/><hi rend="grantha">svasti śrī</hi> <supplied reason="undefined"><g type="ddanda">.</g></supplied> kopparake<hi rend="grantha">sa</hi>ri pa<hi rend="grantha">nma</hi>r<hi rend="grantha">kk</hi>u yāṇṭu Eḻāvatu nāḷ <gap reason="lost" quantity="4" unit="character"/> nūṟṟut toṇṇūṟṟu Eṭṭu paṭuvūrkoṭṭattu kāvitipākkamākiya Amaṉinārāyaṇa<unclear>ca</unclear>tu<hi rend="grantha">rvve</hi>timaṅkalattu Ivāṭ<unclear>ṭ</unclear>ai kuṭumpuvāriyapperumakkaḷum Erivāriyapperumakkaḷum toṭṭavāriyapperumakkaḷum <gap reason="lost" quantity="9" unit="character"/> makkaḷum <hi rend="grantha">bha</hi>ṭṭarkaḷum <gap reason="lost" quantity="7" unit="character"/> 
<lb n="2"/>yārpaṇiyāl Ivvāṇṭu <gap reason="lost" quantity="9" unit="character"/> kki <gap reason="lost" quantity="4" unit="character"/> Erivāriyapperumakkaḷom Emmuryāḷuṅkaṇattāruḷ <gap reason="lost" quantity="5" unit="character"/> ruttu ceṟuvukku mātam pūti <hi rend="grantha">kra</hi><supplied reason="omitted">ma</supplied>vitta<supplied reason="omitted">r</supplied> tām muḷḷapoḻutey tirukkara purattup perumāṉaṭikaḷukku<hi rend="grantha">ācantra</hi> kālamum muṭṭāme Oru nantā viḷakku Erippa<note n="92-1">The next three lines are completely reased.</note> <gap reason="lost" quantity="7" unit="character"/> 
